No later than August 1, 1990, the Cabinet for Health and Family Services shall begin contracting to construct and operate, or lease and operate the following:
A one hundred (100) bed inpatient mental health facility in eastern Kentucky;
Twelve (12) child-care centers with a minimum of one (1) center in each of the six (6) Kentucky congressional districts;
Four (4) eight (8) bed group homes for individuals with an intellectual disability;
Two (2) one hundred (100) bed personal care homes; and
Twelve (12) senior citizens centers with a minimum of one (1) center in each of the six (6) Kentucky congressional districts.
